      {
        "feedback": "While these sentences have a pattern, focus on where は appears. It's not at the end - it comes after the first word or phrase, marking what we're talking about.",
        "isCorrect": false,
        "text": "は always appears at the end of the sentence"
      },
      {
        "feedback": "When は is a particle, it's always pronounced 'wa'. But that's about pronunciation. Look at what role は plays - where does it appear and what comes before it?",
        "isCorrect": false,
        "text": "は is pronounced 'ha' when marking topics"
      }
    ],
    "question": "Looking at the highlighted particle は in these sentences, what pattern do you notice?"
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "highlight": "は",
      "romanization": "watashi wa gakusei desu.",
      "sentence": "私は学生です。",
      "translation": "I am a student."
